73
00:05:44,820 --> 00:05:48,700
No, no, that's not it. We're in the same trade. I also make deliveries.

74
00:05:48,700 --> 00:05:50,630
We're in the same field.

75
00:05:50,630 --> 00:05:52,130
Which platform are you doing deliveries for?

76
00:05:52,130 --> 00:05:55,650
My mom's own store. We produce and deliver ourselves.

77
00:05:55,650 --> 00:05:58,100
Then continue. I, an uncle, need to move on to the next delivery.

78
00:05:58,100 --> 00:06:00,250
Wait wait.

79
00:06:00,250 --> 00:06:03,060
Do you know where Building 18 is at?

80
00:06:03,060 --> 00:06:05,270
I've looked for it for ages and I still can't find it.

81
00:06:05,270 --> 00:06:09,060
Building 18 is on the other side. You can follow me.

82
00:06:09,060 --> 00:06:12,230
Wait for me! Wait!

83
00:06:15,440 --> 00:06:17,470
Wait for me!

84
00:06:23,130 --> 00:06:26,350
Winona Guoguo Food Delivery

85
00:06:32,460 --> 00:06:34,320
Weren't you going way too fast?

86
00:06:34,320 --> 00:06:36,060
You're just too slow.

87
00:06:36,060 --> 00:06:37,990
See? Building 18.

88
00:06:37,990 --> 00:06:39,150
Building 18

89
00:06:40,030 --> 00:06:41,930
Thanks.

90
00:06:41,930 --> 00:06:44,360
You need to say, "Thank you, Uncle".

91
00:07:21,790 --> 00:07:22,960
I got it.

92
00:07:22,960 --> 00:07:24,950
I will deliver that right away.

93
00:07:29,040 --> 00:07:30,720
Why are you still here?

94
00:07:30,720 --> 00:07:33,330
Lower your voice.

95
00:07:33,330 --> 00:07:34,260
What happened?

96
00:07:34,260 --> 00:07:35,620
Nothing, go away.

97
00:07:35,620 --> 00:07:39,430
Who are you talking to? Stop dawdling.

98
00:07:39,430 --> 00:07:41,790
Okay, I got it, I got it.

99
00:08:02,770 --> 00:08:04,860
Auntie.

100
00:08:05,510 --> 00:08:07,700
Hey, Miaomiao. What are you doing here?

101
00:08:07,700 --> 00:08:10,010
I'm helping my mom make deliveries.

102
00:08:10,010 --> 00:08:12,650
It's such a hot day and you're making deliveries. It must be hard work, isn't it?

103
00:08:12,650 --> 00:08:14,250
It's okay, it's not hard.

104
00:08:14,250 --> 00:08:15,560
Seeing you working like this makes my heart hurt a little bit.

105
00:08:15,560 --> 00:08:17,500
What are you doing here?
(Formal Voice)

106
00:08:17,500 --> 00:08:21,050
Oh, do you know where Building 17 is?

107
00:08:21,050 --> 00:08:22,370
I've been looking for it all day.

108
00:08:22,370 --> 00:08:26,040
Your Teacher Liang has a student that signed up to take his art class but has never shown up.

109
00:08:26,040 --> 00:08:29,670
I wanted to come to see if he's sick or if something has happened.

110
00:08:29,670 --> 00:08:32,610
Oh, I know. Building 17 is right over there. It took me a while to find it, also.

111
00:08:32,610 --> 00:08:33,770
Why don't I take you there?

112
00:08:33,770 --> 00:08:35,740
Okay.

113
00:08:36,770 --> 00:08:39,610
- Do you need help?
- I'm fine. I got it. Okay, let's go. That way.

114
00:08:42,240 --> 00:08:44,860
How are you doing in your classes lately?

115
00:08:44,860 --> 00:08:47,320
I'm doing okay. The semester is about to start.

116
00:08:47,320 --> 00:08:50,160
Okay, feel free to come to our house if there's anything you need help with.

117
00:08:57,460 --> 00:08:58,530
Let's go.

118
00:08:58,530 --> 00:08:59,940
Why did you come back?

119
00:08:59,940 --> 00:09:04,070
I won't be able to make it to my last order on time. Can you take me there on your electric scooter?

120
00:09:04,070 --> 00:09:05,820
Do it yourself. I don't have time.

121
00:09:05,820 --> 00:09:08,650
Can you lend me your scooter then?

122
00:09:09,930 --> 00:09:10,890
You know how to drive it?

123
00:09:10,890 --> 00:09:14,000
Yes, my dad taught me in the past.

124
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:19,590
Furthermore, there's not a single person out on the street right now.

125
00:09:19,590 --> 00:09:22,550
I can just practice driving around a couple of times.

126
00:09:22,550 --> 00:09:23,510
There's no one?

127
00:09:23,510 --> 00:09:25,390
No one.

128
00:09:26,390 --> 00:09:28,820
Come on quick.

129
00:09:28,820 --> 00:09:32,720
I can't wait to show off my driving skills.

130
00:09:49,180 --> 00:09:51,680
Can you go slower than this?

131
00:09:52,250 --> 00:09:53,970
Don't talk to me,

132
00:09:53,970 --> 00:09:57,520
I am driving. It's too dangerous.

133
00:09:57,520 --> 00:09:59,790
No worries. At this speed of yours,

134
00:09:59,790 --> 00:10:03,320
what you need to worry about isn't danger but your feet.

135
00:10:16,200 --> 00:10:20,210
Sit tight. My orders are always delivered on time.

136
00:10:21,430 --> 00:10:23,680
Lin Kaituo!

137
00:10:23,680 --> 00:10:25,840
I don't want to die yet, I still haven't gone to college!

138
00:10:25,840 --> 00:10:27,740
I don't mind paying the late fee, go slower!

139
00:10:27,740 --> 00:10:30,570
All right, don't get too excited.

140
00:10:34,470 --> 00:10:36,160
Lin Kaituo!

141
00:10:36,960 --> 00:10:38,620
Fine, fine, fine.

142
00:10:38,620 --> 00:10:40,730
Sit tight, and let's go!

143
00:10:44,910 --> 00:10:48,900
Okay... Okay, I like this speed. Keep it like this.

144
00:10:49,430 --> 00:10:51,970
That's pretty good.

145
00:11:13,120 --> 00:11:16,120
Here, your delivery fee.

146
00:11:17,710 --> 00:11:20,640
This is it for my delivery fee?

147
00:11:23,490 --> 00:11:26,180
Then I'll give you both.

148
00:11:47,550 --> 00:11:50,380
Then I'll get going.

149
00:11:50,380 --> 00:11:53,390
I still need to get my bicycle.

150
00:11:55,530 --> 00:11:59,300
- Thanks... for today.
- What?

151
00:12:03,380 --> 00:12:05,320
Just, thanks for today.

152
00:12:06,890 --> 00:12:08,790
Hurry and disappear.

153
00:12:17,900 --> 00:12:23,860
Thank you for helping me avoid embarrassment today, so my mom didn't have to see me making deliveries.

154
00:12:47,840 --> 00:12:49,560
- Quickly come in.
- I'll take that.

155
00:12:49,560 --> 00:12:50,710
You can't fit anything else in.

156
00:12:50,710 --> 00:12:54,310
Why are we preparing Kaituo's luggage already?

157
00:12:54,310 --> 00:12:58,950
I start packing early. Just in case something is forgotten, there's still time to look for it.

158
00:12:58,950 --> 00:13:04,390
The school is very close. If he leaves anything behind, he can always come back and get it.

159
00:13:04,390 --> 00:13:07,630
It's not like you don't know what kind of child Xiao Tuo is.

160
00:13:07,630 --> 00:13:11,630
Once he leaves, we won't know when he'll even be willing to come back.

161
00:13:11,630 --> 00:13:16,370
He's a boy. He'll get better as he matures.

162
00:13:16,370 --> 00:13:19,760
Oh, this is the rent he will pay for two years.

163
00:13:19,760 --> 00:13:22,000
Where do you want to keep it?

164
00:13:24,390 --> 00:13:27,310
- You can put it in that drawer.
- Okay.

165
00:13:27,310 --> 00:13:31,580
Okay. Judging from his personality, he won't come to pick it up even if we put it there.

166
00:13:34,060 --> 00:13:37,230
He has never asked for money.

167
00:13:37,860 --> 00:13:43,070
It's good even if he doesn't get it, he can use it if there's an emergency.

168
00:13:44,980 --> 00:13:48,920
I saw Xia Miaomiao making deliveries today.

169
00:13:49,650 --> 00:13:52,670
I wondered... if Xiao Tuo was also working this hard every day?

170
00:13:52,670 --> 00:13:57,050
I wondered... if Xiao Tuo was also working this hard every day?

171
00:13:57,050 --> 00:14:00,120
Don't worry too much, he's a man.

172
00:14:00,120 --> 00:14:02,690
It's good for him to go through some hardship.

173
00:14:03,920 --> 00:14:07,920
Younian also said he wouldn't come back home for the summer.

174
00:14:07,920 --> 00:14:10,810
He said he wanted to go explore the mountains and collect local cultural materials or something.

175
00:14:10,810 --> 00:14:13,240
Of course, I supported him.

176
00:14:13,900 --> 00:14:18,600
Even if you say it, it's still hard not to worry.

177
00:14:19,460 --> 00:14:26,440
Wife, if you want to overthink why don't we think about what we're going to have for dinner tonight. Okay?

178
00:14:26,440 --> 00:14:28,980
You only know to eat. Help me tidy things up.

179
00:14:28,980 --> 00:14:30,460
Once you're done with that, I'll make dinner for you.

180
00:14:30,460 --> 00:14:32,570
All right! As you wish!

181
00:14:36,280 --> 00:14:38,170
- Put the coat there.
- Okay.

